<ol class="blogroll wp-dark-mode-bg-image">
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54556" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://ejpe.org/journal/article/view/1007/746" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“Combining economics with philosophy makes for an excellent and productive career”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; that&#8217;s advice for graduate students from John Broome, but it might also be a summary of this in-depth interview with him about his education and work</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54555" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://nautil.us/the-philosophy-of-tyranny-1229763/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“The fantasy that you can just wipe away democratic traditions and get something in its place that will solve the problems of democracy is a very dangerous one that Plato fell victim to”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; on Plato&#8217;s real world attempts to influence government</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54554" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2025-08-08/ty-article/.premium/top-court-justice-rebuked-for-attending-event-honoring-academic-critical-of-gaza-war/00000198-887b-da02-ab98-ddfb9edc0000" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“Israel’s State Ombudsman for Judges admonished [a] Supreme Court Justice for speaking at a conference honoring a Hebrew University professor who has criticized the war in Gaza”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; the professor? philosopher David Enoch</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54526" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://grecowansley.substack.com/p/biting-bullets" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“Better to work with a theory that doesn’t accommodate all the data, if that’s the cost of explaining some of them”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Daniel Greco on (Timothy Williamson on) bullet-biting and philosophy</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54525" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2025/08/03/us/campus-reform-college-protests-antisemitism-zachary-marschall.html?smid=nytcore-ios-share&amp;referringSource=articleShare" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“More than 40 percent [of over 200 people targeted by Campus Reform one year] said they had received threats of physical violence”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; the NYT on the conservative groups threatening freedom of expression in higher education</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54523" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://hiphination.substack.com/p/when-should-you-peak" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“Interesting lives make good stories, not the other way around”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Barry Lam on the age at which it&#8217;s best to &#8220;peak&#8221; and what can be learned from thinking about that</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54524" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.pnas.org/doi/10.1073/pnas.2500322122" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“Publication rates rise sharply during the tenure-track, peaking just before tenure… After tenure, faculty produce more novel works, though fewer highly cited papers”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; a new study on the impact of tenure on faculty research trajectories</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54503" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://scottaaronson.blog/?p=9030" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“A future without work could be much better than ours, overall. But, living in that world, or watching as our old ways passed away, we might still reasonably grieve the loss of the work that once was part of who we were”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Harvey Lederman on the dread he feels about the omni-automation on the horizon</span></li>
</ol>
<p>Mini-Heap posts usually appear when several new items accumulate in the <a class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://dailynous.com/heap-of-links/">Heap of Links</a>, a collection of items from around the web that may be of interest to philosophers. The Heap of Links consists partly of suggestions from readers; if you find something online that you think would be of interest to the philosophical community, please <a class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="mailto:dailynouseditor@gmail.com">send it in</a> for consideration for the Heap. Thank you.<br class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" /><a class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://dailynous.com/2025/08/05/mini-heap-670/">Previous edition</a>.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/08/14/mini-heap-671/">Mini-Heap</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>